# TwinCAT MCP Build Automation

## Available MCP Tools

### Requires TcXaeShell (XAE)

| Tool | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `twincat_status` | Check if XAE is installed / running |
| `twincat_open` | Open solution in XAE, locate PLC project |
| `twincat_check_all_objects` | Compile ALL objects — returns `error_count`, `warning_count`, `errors[]`, `warnings[]`, `infos[]` directly |
| `twincat_build` | Full rebuild of the solution |
| `twincat_get_output_log` | Read errors/warnings from last `twincat_build` (not needed after `twincat_check_all_objects`) |
| `twincat_reload` | Close + reopen solution (re-reads structural files from disk) |
| `twincat_export_library` | Export `.library` + `.compiled-library` |
| `twincat_close` | Release session (never closes user solutions) |

### No XAE needed (pure file operations)

| Tool | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `twincat_plcproj_info` | Read version/title from `.plcproj` |
| `twincat_plcproj_verify` | Verify `.plcproj` matches disk |
| `twincat_plcproj_sync` | Sync `.plcproj` from disk — force/dry-run/backup |
| `twincat_migrate` | Auto-detect FBD/CFC, convert to ST in one pass |
| `twincat_fup_migrate` | Convert FBD/FUP to ST |
| `twincat_cfc_migrate` | Convert CFC to ST |

## When to Validate

After editing `.TcPOU`, `.TcDUT`, or `.TcGVL` files, validate with:

1. `twincat_open` (with explicit `plcproj_path`)
2. `twincat_check_all_objects` — errors, warnings, and infos are included in the response
3. Fix errors → repeat from step 2

`twincat_get_output_log` is only needed after `twincat_build`. Do NOT call it after `twincat_check_all_objects` — the response already contains all diagnostics.

For the detailed workflow, use the `twincat3-validate` skill.

## Critical Rules

- **Always pass explicit `plcproj_path`** to `twincat_open`. Auto-detect is unreliable in multi-project workspaces.
- **No `twincat_reload` needed** after editing `.TcPOU` / `.TcDUT` / `.TcGVL` content — `twincat_check_all_objects` reads directly from disk.
- **`twincat_reload` IS required** after structural changes to `.plcproj`, `.tsproj`, or `.sln` (added/removed files, version bumps, library references).
- **Use `twincat_check_all_objects`** for library projects — it compiles every object. A normal `twincat_build` only compiles objects reachable from MAIN.

## Do NOT call `twincat_close`

The TwinCAT XAE solution should **stay open** between tool calls. Starting XAE and loading a solution takes significant time (~10-30 s), so keeping the session alive avoids unnecessary delays.

**Never call `twincat_close`** unless:
- TwinCAT XAE is completely unresponsive (COM calls time out or crash repeatedly).
- The user explicitly asks to close or quit XAE.

In normal workflows (validate, build, export, reload) simply leave the session open. The next `twincat_open` call will reuse the running instance automatically.
